osed_at":"2024-11-30T19:28:34Z","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"Not sure, maybe this can already be set up, but some labs will have 100+ tools, is there a way to add tables that can be searched ? ","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/galaxyproject/galaxy_codex/issues/236/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/galaxyproject/galaxy_codex/issues/236/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/galaxyproject/galaxy_codex/issues/comments/2509165696","html_url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/galaxy_codex/issues/236#issuecomment-2509165696","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/galaxyproject/galaxy_codex/issues/236","id":2509165696,"node_id":"IC_kwDOIQitUM6VjtSA","user":{"login":"neoformit","id":42562517,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQyNTYyNTE3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/42562517?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/neoformit","html_url":"https://github.com/neoformit","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/neoformit/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/neoformit/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/neoformit/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/neoformit/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/neoformit/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/neoformit/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/neoformit/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/neoformit/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/neoformit/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-11-30T19:28:34Z","updated_at":"2024-11-30T19:28:34Z","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"To be clear - *you can already include custom HTML snippets* in your Lab page. This is enough to build the feature that you are asking for. It's not the job of the Labs Engine to provide every web component that might be useful in a Galaxy Lab. If you want something fancy, some web development is required. If you think this is something every Lab might benefit from, you are welcome to make a pull request to [usegalaxy-au/galaxy-labs-engine](https://github.com/usegalaxy-au/galaxy-labs-engine).

Tool metadata as JSON (this can live anywhere in the repo):
```js
[
    {
        "tool_name": "Kraken2",
        "tool_description": "Taxonomic classification of metagenomic sequences."
    },
    {
        "tool_name": "MetaPhlAn",
        "tool_description": "Profiling the composition of microbial communities."
    },
    {
        "tool_name": "FastQC",
        "tool_description": "Quality control tool for high throughput sequence data."
    }
]
```

HTML snippet (include in your Lab's `conclusion.html`):
```html
<div>
    <table id="toolsTable">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Tool Name</th>
                <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <!-- Rows will be dynamically inserted here -->
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <script>
        const JSON_URL = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/galaxyproject/galaxy_codex/refs/heads/main/communities/microgalaxy/metadata/tools.json'
        async function fetchAndRenderTools() {
            try {
                // Fetch the JSON file
                const response = await fetch(JSON_URL);
                if (!response.ok) {
                    throw new Error(`HTTP error! Status: ${response.status}`);
                }

                const tools = await response.json();

                // Reference the table body
                const tableBody = document.getElementById('toolsTable').querySelector('tbody');

                // Populate the table with tools
                tools.forEach(tool => {
                    const row = document.createElement('tr');
                    row.innerHTML = `
                        <td>${tool.tool_name}</td>
                        <td>${tool.tool_description}</td>
                    `;
                    tableBody.appendChild(row);
                });
            } catch (error) {
                console.error('Error fetching or rendering tools:', error);
            }
        }

        // Call the function to fetch and render tools
        fetchAndRenderTools();
    </script>
</div>
```","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/galaxyproject/galaxy_codex/issues/comments/2509165696/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}}

